I need to identify the profit after all expenses have been deducted from total revenue, which is the Net Profit in the income statement. Then I need to identify 5 component sub-items that contribute to this calculation.

Looking at the income statement:
1. The Net Profit is 111731.83
2. This is calculated as Profit Before Tax (151331.49) minus Tax Expense (39599.66)
3. The Profit Before Tax is calculated from several components

The 5 key sub-items that contribute to the Net Profit calculation are:
1. Total Revenue: 791992.51
2. Cost of Goods Sold: 504930.00
3. Total Expenses: 140995.72
4. Interest Income: 5264.70
5. Tax Expense: 39599.66

The formula would be: Net Profit = Total Revenue - Cost of Goods Sold - Total Expenses + Interest Income - Tax Expense
791992.51 - 504930.00 - 140995.72 + 5264.70 - 39599.66 = 111731.83
